rComments: I'll be honest about Professor Brown. I found his lectures pretty interesting, even though it was at 8:30 or 10am.. The papers were very challenging, but they really challenge how well you can research. Final was based on real international events happening (Spoiler alert).. make sure apply your textbook knowledge then. Overall I'm glad I had him.

He is a decent professor. His lectures can be a little disorganized but attending them and taking notes are crucial since his slides have minimal material on them. The textbook helps if you need clarification in certain areas. The papers were fair but the exam was very difficult.
the worst prof I have ever had..... DO NOT REPLY Emails, release marks extremely slowly!!!!!!!! Not helping at all!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  Avoid him!!!! The worst prof ever!!!!!!!
He is not always replying the emails, which is kinda frustrating..
Final exam was extremely difficult. But very good professor and should be your top choice for int business course.

No midterm, two fairly long papers, 5 & 7 pages single spaced. The classes are intriguing and you'll want to go. The slides don't always explain what you are expected to know. Very easy to understand, logical, approachable. 8/10 would recommend.
Encourages discussion based learning which can making for interesting lectures. Better than the other options for IB. Hard to get a really high mark though when there are only two papers and a final.
